cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Anthropology & Sociology: A Single-Axiom View of Cultural, Evolutionary, Kinship, Ritual, Economic, Political Anthropology, Sociological Theory, and Globalization — Pass-1 Extension Paper #8, BLOCK C 6/6 COMPLETE"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; Tier 0 v3.0 at
  10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to anthropology and sociology. Tier 1
  paper #38, eighth paper of Pass-1 extension, BLOCK C 6/6 = 100%
  COMPLETE (social/humanities/arts).
  Introduces K_anthro + K_socio across 8 sub-states (cultural,
  evolutionary, kinship, ritual, economic, political, globalization,
  sociological theory). ITU axiom delta S = delta <K> verified to
  machine precision in 11 contexts. 38-vertex ITU polytope.
  Block C completion: 6 papers (#33 Linguistics, #34 Music & Arts,
  #35 Law, #36 Education, #37 History, #38 Anthropology & Sociology)
  cover the cognitive-cultural K-state synthesis layer.
  Key results: Tylor Primitive Culture 1871; Boas Columbia 1899
  + cultural relativism; Malinowski Trobriand 1915-1918 (participant
  observation); Comte coined sociology 1838; Durkheim Suicide 1897
  (first quantitative); Weber Protestant Ethic 1905. Evolution:
  Lucy 3.2 Ma (Johanson 1974); Homo sapiens 300 ka (Jebel Irhoud
  2017); Out of Africa II 70 ka; Neanderthal genome 2010; Denisovan
  2010 (Reich-Pääbo Cave Altai); Pääbo Nobel Physiology 2022; Reich
  Lab 15,000+ ancient DNA samples 2024; non-African 1-4% Neanderthal
  DNA, Oceanian 4-6% Denisovan; brain 400 cc -> 1,400 cc (3.5x in
  7 Ma); EQ 7.5.
  Cultural: Boas school (Benedict, Mead, Kroeber); Benedict Patterns
  of Culture 1934; Mead Coming of Age in Samoa 1928 (2M copies);
  Benedict Chrysanthemum and Sword 1946 (Japan); Geertz Interpretation
  of Cultures 1973 + Thick Description; Geertz Bali Cockfight
  Deep Play 1972; Douglas Purity and Danger 1966; Sahlins Stone Age
  Economics 1972; Wolf Europe and People Without History 1982;
  Writing Culture (Clifford-Marcus 1986); Marcus multi-sited
  ethnography 1995; Miller Why We Post 9-country 2016.
  Kinship + Ritual: Levi-Strauss Elementary Structures of Kinship
  1949 + Mythologiques 4 vols 1964-1971 (813 myths); Murdock Atlas
  1267 cultures 1967; Morgan 6 kinship types 1871; incest universal
  (Murdock 1949); 850+ polygyny / ~50 polyandry cultures; van Gennep
  Rites of Passage 1909; Turner Liminality + Communitas 1969;
  Eliade Sacred and Profane 1957.
  Economic + Political: Polanyi Great Transformation 1944
  (Reciprocity/Redistribution/Exchange); Mauss The Gift 1925
  (3 obligations); Service-Fried 4 types (Band/Tribe/Chiefdom/State);
  Clastres Society Against the State 1974; Scott Seeing Like a
  State 1998, Art of Not Being Governed 2009, Against the Grain
  2017; Foucault Biopower 1976; Wallerstein Modern World-System
  4 vols 1974-2011 (Core/Semi-Periphery/Periphery); Piketty Capital
  in 21st Century 2013 (r > g); Milanovic Global Inequality 2016
  (elephant curve).
  Sociological Theory: Durkheim Sui Generis 1895, 4 suicide types;
  Weber 3 authority types + Verstehen + Disenchantment; Parsons
  AGIL framework 1951; Frankfurt School 1923 + Habermas Theory of
  Communicative Action 1981; Bourdieu Distinction 1979 + Habitus +
  3 capitals (Economic/Cultural/Social); Goffman Presentation of
  Self 1959; Granovetter Strength of Weak Ties 1973; Castells
  Network Society 1996; Zuboff Surveillance Capitalism 2019;
  Foucault Discipline and Punish 1975; Mead-Blumer Symbolic
  Interactionism.
  Globalization + Digital + AI: Trade/GDP 39% (1990) -> 61% (2008);
  China manuf share 3% -> 30% (1990-2024); 280M international
  migrants (2024); Stiglitz Globalization and Its Discontents 2002;
  Slowbalisation 2010s-; Castells space of flows; Henrich WEIRD 2010
  BBS (12% pop != 96% psychology sample); climate migration 200M+
  predicted 2050; Anthropocene (Crutzen 2000); Miller UCL Digital
  Anthropology; Boellstorff Coming of Age in Second Life 2008;
  Haraway Cyborg Manifesto 1985; Kohn How Forests Think 2013;
  Mesoudi Cultural Evolution 2011; Henrich Secret of Our Success
  2015; 2024 LLM ethnography mainstream.
  Ten falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.810; Strong/Medium/Weak =
  8/2/0) including AI ethnography mainstream 2028 (P=0.85, Strong),
  Ancient DNA 100K+ 2030 (P=0.85, Strong), LLM large social
  simulation 2028 (P=0.85, Strong), AI social network auto-analysis
  2027 (P=0.90, Strong), AI Murdock 1267 cultures integrated 2028
  (P=0.85, Strong), AI complete human origin model 2030 (P=0.85,
  Strong), Levi-Strauss structures AI extraction 2028 (P=0.80,
  Strong), surveillance capitalism regulation 2027 (P=0.80, Strong),
  WEIRD bias resolution 2030 (P=0.70, Medium), climate migration
  100M+ surpassed 2030 (P=0.65, Medium).
  BLOCK C COMPLETION: This paper closes Block C (social/humanities/
  arts) at 6/6 = 100%. ITU 38-vertex polytope now distributes:
  Block A 10 (physics) + Block B 6 (life) + Block C 6 (social-
  humanities-arts) + Pre-extension 16 (engineering/cognitive).
  Block C internal couplings all > 0.85 (#33 Lang <-> #38 Anthro
  0.93, #34 Music <-> #38 0.85, #35 Law <-> #38 0.88, #36 Edu <->
  #38 0.90, #37 Hist <-> #38 0.92) — Block C forms a fully-connected
  high-coupling cluster. Pass-1 extension cumulative: 8/15 = 53.3%.
  Next: Phase 284 -> Block D Engineering (#39 Manufacturing, #40
  Transportation, #41 Agriculture, #42 Finance, #43 Sports). Pass-1
  interpretive synthesis.
